# Daytona Playground

This repository contains a simple web-based "Daytona Playground" demo that emulates editing the GitHub Pages for octocat's Hello-World.

## Features

- **Authentication**: single hard-coded user (email `solomonubani1987@gmail.com`, password `cgames`).
- **Content Editing**: users can edit playground text and save it; each save generates a unique Game ID and persists it in `localStorage`.
- **Game Store**: accessible via a store icon (one of the workspace images). Logged-in users can upload game executables, which are listed with their Game ID. Uploads cannot be edited or deleted.
- **Checkout**: each uploaded game shows a "Checkout (£11)" button that opens PayPal to send £11 to `solomonubani1987@gmail.com`.
- **Simple data storage**: All state is kept in `localStorage` so content persists between page loads.

The source files for the playground are located under `daytona-playground/`:

```text
- index.html
- styles.css
- app.js
```

Open `daytona-playground/index.html` in a browser to try the playground.

